article.description: Shavonte Zellous scored 31 points to lead Pittsburgh to a 97-68 win over No. 15 DePaul on Sunday.
article.headline: Zellous feeds Pitt's win over No. 15 DePaul with 31 points
article.linkText: Pitt breezes by No. 15 DePaul behind Zellous' 31
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Shavonte Zellous scored 31 points to lead Pittsburgh to a 97-68 win over No. 15 DePaul on Sunday.

Pittsburgh (11-3) took the lead from the start and never relinquished it. It went into halftime with a 43-29 advantage.

Mercedes Walker had 15 points and a game-high 12 rebounds for Pitt. Jania Sims chipped in 11 points and Xenia Stewart added 10.

Allie Quigley and Caprice Smith led the Blue Demons (11-3) with 15 points each. Deirdre Naughton scored 13 and Natasha Williams added 10.

Pittsburgh's reserves outscored DePaul's substitutes 30-12.

The Panthers shot consistently better than DePaul, making 56.8 percent (21-of-37) of their shots from the field in the second half. That compared to DePaul's 38.7 percent (12-of-31) after the break.
